    <h1>Customising the tab names</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Did you know that you can customise some aspects of your plentymarkets system?
This page teaches you how to customise the names of tabs.</p>
</div>
<h5 id="_what_exactly_is_it_about" class="discrete">What exactly is it about?</h5>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When you <a href="/en/item/introduction/search#100">search for items</a>, you’ll see the results displayed in an overview.
Click on one of these items to open it in a new tab.
The item ID is displayed in this tab by default.
But you can decide if you’d rather see the item’s name or number in the tab.
Of course you can change these settings at any time.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Further customisation options</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also decide, e.g.:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/welcome/customise-system#160">which columns</a> should be displayed in the item overview.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>whether the item information should be displayed in <a href="/en/welcome/customise-system#170">ascending or descending order</a>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
